The DERBY OIL COMPANY, a Corporation, v. UNIVERSAL OIL PRODUCTS COMPANY, a Corporation. No. 1815. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. Jan. 23, 1939. Yankey, Osborne & Sears, of Wichita, Kan., for appellant. Smith, Hatcher & McFarland, of Topeka, Kan., and R. R. Brewster, of Kansas City, Mo., for appellee.

Before LEWIS and PHILLIPS, Circuit Judges. .

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed at appellant’s costs, pursuant to stipulation. * -
